NEXT RELEASE:

1) new stuff
    a) Implement new xml config
            i) re-write filter stuff to go with the xml config
                a) duplicates, missing elements etc
                b) improve read/write filter stuff and tidy
                c) test all the filtering of mails, including Cc: and To:
                d) convert to a GSList
            ii) tidy of xml stuff
                a) re-write write routines similar to read, i.e have a elist array.  This will allow elements to be defined once in a single place
            iii) final cleanup/testing (with valgrind)
    b) proxy server option?

2) Compile/test on win32
    a) After xml stuff is done, get it all to compile on win32
    b) Test it all works, port any stuff back if needed
    c) Use Nullsoft scriptable installer as an installer and test.
    d) Sort out error/warnings in src/*.c.  Should probably use err_dlg, or warn_dlg unless GTK is not running, then report in text mode.
    e) Make sure GtkStatusIcon stuff is correct.

2) Test with valgrind:
    valgrind needs to be run as follows:

    G_SLICE=always-malloc G_DEBUG=gc-friendly valgrind --leak-check=full --error-limit=no

    NOTE: currently g_module_open() dlopen() are reporting errors, need to investigate this
    (e.g write small app that calls dlopen to check whether problem is specific to mailtc)

    a) everything plugin related
    b) the message list/header adding
    c) config file reading/writing
    d) pop stuff
    e) filter stuff
    f) localisation stuff
    g) connection error stuff
    h) run command on new mail stuff
    i) IMAP stuff.  NOTE mark as read stuff needs full heavy testing.
